[SN]TITLE[SN]
IPCC to probe police contact with murder victim

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The police watchdog is to investigate what contact South Wales Police had with a murder victim prior to the discovery of her body.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The body of 65-year-old Christine James was found in her flat in Cardiff Bay on 2 March after she failed to arrive for a flight.
Kris Wade, 36, of Cardiff, has been charged with her murder.
South Wales Police referred the case to the Independent Police Complaints Commission.
